  "body": "After installing nginx on the kubernetes master (currently non-k8s docker container) and forwarding external http requests  to the kubernetes-ro service through nginx with simple htpasswd auth, I tested it (to use within CI tool), but it failed to pass nginx.\n\n```\n/tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f master_ip=54.X.X.X\n/tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f wget https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v0.8.1/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl\n--2015-01-28 23:53:43--  https://storage.googleapis.com/kubernetes-release/release/v0.8.1/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl\nResolving storage.googleapis.com (storage.googleapis.com)... 74.125.235.106, 74.125.235.108, 74.125.235.107\nConnecting to storage.googleapis.com (storage.googleapis.com)|74.125.235.106|:443... connected.\nHTTP request sent, awaiting response... 200 OK\nLength: 12221288 (12M) [application/octet-stream]\nSaving to: \u2018kubectl\u2019\n\nkubectl                                         100%[========================================================================================================>]  11.65M  5.18MB/s   in 2.2s\n\n2015-01-28 23:53:45 (5.18 MB/s) - \u2018kubectl\u2019 saved [12221288/12221288]\n\n/tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f chmod +x kubectl                                                                                                                                                                    \n/tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f ./kubectl get --insecure-skip-tls-verify=true -s $master_ip -a ~/.kubernetes_auth pods\nF0128 23:54:34.151603   17748 get.go:75] request [&{Method:GET URL:http://54.X.X.X/api/v1beta1/pods?namespace=default Proto:HTTP/1.1 ProtoMajor:1 ProtoMinor:1 Header:map[] Body:<nil> ContentLength:0 TransferEncoding:[] Close:false Host:54.X.X.X Form:map[] PostForm:map[] MultipartForm:<nil> Trailer:map[] RemoteAddr: RequestURI: TLS:<nil>}] failed (401) 401 Unauthorized: <html>\n<head><title>401 Authorization Required</title></head>\n<body bgcolor=\"white\">\n<center><h1>401 Authorization Required</h1></center>\n<hr><center>nginx/1.6.2</center>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n/tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f curl -u $(cat ~/.kubernetes_auth) $master_ip\n<html><body>Welcome to Kubernetes</body></html>%                                                                                                                                               /tmp \u276f\u276f\u276f\n```\n\nIs it because we are required to use https when querying the apiserver using kubectl? Or because the -a option is used for a different auth ?\nHow would you solve this issue ?\n\nThank you in advance!\n",
